messages.message:
How can I silence or fix `mypy` warnings about generated `pb2.py` files?

```instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1017: error: Module has no attribute "_CONTEXT"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1018: error: Module has no attribute "_CONTEXT"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1021: error: Module has no attribute "_CONTEXT"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1025: error: Module has no attribute "_CONTEXT"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1028: error: Module has no attribute "_CONTEXT"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1029: error: Module has no attribute "_CONTEXT"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1141: error: "GeneratedProtocolMessageType" has no attribute "PaginationOptions"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1163: error: "GeneratedProtocolMessageType" has no attribute "PaginationOptions"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1202: error: Unexpected keyword argument "create_key" for "ServiceDescriptor"
instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/ai_hub_service_pb2.py:1208: error: Module has no attribute "_internal_create_key"```
I tried regenerating the stubs, with no luck.
Weird. Reading the code there, I'd have thought that it would ignore this file, since it's in `instabase/protos` and ends with `pb2.py`

```diff --git a/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/scripts/run_mypy.py b/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/scripts/run_mypy.py
index 2a3af57602..16be4ecc43 100644
--- a/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/scripts/run_mypy.py
+++ b/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/scripts/run_mypy.py
@@ -77,7 +77,9 @@ ignore_files = frozenset([
     # Test code that contains thrift/proto files
     'test_copy.py',
     'test_mount_client.py',
-    'test_account_client.py'
+    'test_account_client.py',
+    'test_sdk.py',
+    'ai_hub_service_pb2_grpc.py',
 ])```
